# 🎯 Today's Goal

Build a small hospital database.

Instead of storing one patient...

```python
patient = {
    "Name": "Alice",
    "Age": 24
}
```

We'll store **many patients**.

```python
hospital = [

    {
        "Name": "Alice",
        "Age":24
    },

    {
        "Name":"Bob",
        "Age":35
    },

    {
        "Name":"Charlie",
        "Age":50
    }

]
```

Notice

Hospital

↓

contains

↓

Many Patients

↓

Each Patient

↓

is a Dictionary.

---

# Visualize It

```
hospital
│
├── Patient 1
│      Name → Alice
│      Age → 24
│
├── Patient 2
│      Name → Bob
│      Age → 35
│
└── Patient 3
       Name → Charlie
       Age → 50
```

This is exactly how your Blood Report App will store data before saving it into a database.

