# 🧠 Today's Theory

## List

Stores multiple values.

Example

```python
numbers = [10,20,30]
```

---

## Dictionary

Stores related information.

Example

```python
patient = {
    "Name":"Alice",
    "Age":24
}
```

---

## List of Dictionaries

Stores multiple patients.

Example

```python
hospital = [

    {
        "Name":"Alice"
    },

    {
        "Name":"Bob"
    }

]
```

---

## Why is this useful?

Your Blood Report App will eventually save data in a database, but before it reaches the database, your program will organize it in structures very similar to this.

Think of it like:

```
User fills form
        ↓
Dictionary created
        ↓
Dictionary added to Hospital List
        ↓
Hospital List sent to Database
```

The database will come much later, but the mindset starts today.

